This paper deals with the design and implementation of a parallel algorithm for Aggregate Risk Analysis, which involves computationally intensive and data-intensive problems. This makes it likely to belong to the categories of Computer Engineering (cs.CE), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), Software Engineering (cs.SE), and Programming Languages (cs.PL).
